  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (31fcf5a 2023-05-19T00:10:33.861185000Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge coverage\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (Apple Silicon)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nHello team, \r\n\r\nI've encountered a potential bug on **calculating branch coverage** while working on my [project](https://github.com/kshyun28/foundry-nft).\r\n\r\nCurrently I cannot get 100% coverage on the branches when running `forge coverage`.\r\n![coverage](https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/assets/56709653/0208fc06-c280-4969-a104-f9e27073bbd1)\r\n\r\nThen when running `forge coverage --report debug`, I get\r\n```bash\r\nCompiler run successful!\r\nAnalysing contracts...\r\nRunning tests...\r\nUncovered for src/MyNFT.sol:\r\n- Branch (branch: 0, path: 1) (location: source ID 29, line 44, chars 1313-1346, hits: 0)\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe culprit is the code below, which is a \"require\" statement that will **always revert**, \r\n```solidity\r\nrequire(false, \"cannot renounce\");\r\n```\r\nbut the coverage report is still expecting a branch where \"require\" **will not revert**. \r\n\r\nI appreciate the team's inputs here if this is expected behavior or a valid bug, and will assist wherever I can.\r\n\r\nMinimal code snippet to reproduce below, then run `forge coverage`.\r\n\r\n**MyNFT.sol**\r\n```solidity\r\n// SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT\r\npragma solidity ^0.8.13;\r\n\r\nimport \"@openzeppelin/utils/Strings.sol\";\r\nimport \"@openzeppelin/token/ERC721/ERC721.sol\";\r\nimport \"@openzeppelin/access/Ownable.sol\";\r\n\r\ncontract MyNFT is ERC721, Ownable {\r\n    constructor() ERC721(\"MyNFT\", \"MN\") {}\r\n\r\n    function renounceOwnership() public pure override {\r\n        require(false, \"cannot renounce\");\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n**MyNFT.t.sol**\r\n```solidity\r\n// SPDX-License-Identifier: UNLICENSED\r\npragma solidity ^0.8.13;\r\n\r\nimport \"forge-std/Test.sol\";\r\nimport \"../src/MyNFT.sol\";\r\n\r\ncontract MyNFTTest is Test {\r\n    MyNFT public myNFT;\r\n\r\n    function setUp() public {\r\n        myNFT = new MyNFT();\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    function testRenounceOwnership() public {\r\n        vm.expectRevert();\r\n        myNFT.renounceOwnership();\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n```",
